<p>This page displays subscriber history events in a similar way to the subscriber history page, but selects all subscribers.</p><table><tr><td>All</td><td>Select all events and display in reverse chronological order, i.e. most recent first.</td></tr><tr><td>Since</td><td>Select all events since the entered date and display in chronological order. The date may be entered in any format that PHP will recognise, such as 2011-10-01 or 1 Oct.</td></tr><tr><td>Contains</td><td>Select all events whose summary or detail contain the entered text and display in chronological order. The text may be a regular expression.</td></tr><tr><td>Event</td><td>The event id.</td></tr><tr><td>Email</td><td>The email address of the subscriber, which is a link to the Subscriber Details page.</td></tr><tr><td>Date</td><td>The date of the event.</td></tr><tr><td>Summary</td><td>The summary of the event.</td></tr><tr><td>Detail</td><td>The detail of the event.</td></tr></table>